subject: p17669276
History: History of CHF, presenting with cough and weakness.
Findings: Frontal and lateral radiographs of the chest were acquired. There is new mild interstitial pulmonary edema. A small right pleural effusion may be minimally increased. There is also likely a trace left pleural effusion. There is no focal consolidation. The heart size is not significantly changed. There is no pneumothorax. Midline sternotomy wires are noted.
Impression: New mild interstitial pulmonary edema. Minimally increased small right pleural effusion and trace left pleural effusion.
